arXiv:2310.11942v2 Announce Type: replace-cross Abstract: T2K is a neutrino oscillation experiment with a 295 km long baseline between the far detector, Super-Kamiokande, and a suite of near detectors to study $
u_\mu/ ar{
u}_\mu$ disappearance and $
u_e/ ar{
u}_e$ appearance in a $
u_\mu/ ar{
u}_\mu$ neutrino beam produced at J-PARC. The experiment has excluded CP conservation in the three-neutrino oscillation model at $>90~\%$ CL and precisely constrained the parameters $\vert \Delta m_{32}^2 \vert$ and $\sin^2 	heta_{23}$. This paper reports on the novelties of the most up-to-date 2022 analysis and the near-future prospects of T2K.
